@startuml auth-login-refresh
' Service : Auth — Inscription, connexion, refresh, déconnexion
' Date : 2026-06-27

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 1.5
skinparam participantPadding 10

' Mise en page A4 portrait
scale max 2480*3508
skinparam defaultFontSize 12

actor "Utilisateur" as User
participant "Browser\n(Next.js)" as Browser
participant "Gateway\n:8080" as GW
participant "Auth svc\n:50051" as AUTH
participant "Users svc\n:50052" as USERS
participant "Email svc\n:50058" as EMAIL
database "DB auth" as DBA
database "DB users" as DBU

== Inscription ==

User -> Browser : Formulaire d'inscription
Browser -> GW : POST /api/auth/register\n{ email, password }
GW -> AUTH : Register(email, password)
AUTH -> DBA : SELECT FROM auth WHERE email (unicité)
AUTH -> DBA : INSERT INTO auth\n(user_id, email, password_hash,\nrole='free_user', account_status='active',\nsubscription_tier='free', email_verified=false,\nsession_version=1)
AUTH -> USERS : CreateUser(user_id, email)
USERS -> DBU : INSERT INTO users(user_id, email)
AUTH -> EMAIL : SendVerificationEmail(user_id, email)
EMAIL -> DBA : INSERT INTO email_verification_tokens\n(user_id, token_hash, expires_at)
AUTH --> GW : FormGenericResponse
GW --> Browser : 201
Browser --> User : "Vérifiez votre email"

== Vérification email ==

User -> Browser : Clic lien email (/verify-email?token=...)
Browser -> GW : POST /api/auth/verify-email\n{ email, token }
GW -> AUTH : VerifyEmail(email, token)
AUTH -> DBA : SELECT FROM email_verification_tokens\n  WHERE token_hash AND expires_at > NOW()
AUTH -> DBA : UPDATE auth SET email_verified=true\nUPDATE email_verification_tokens SET used_at=NOW()
AUTH --> GW : OK
GW --> Browser : 200
Browser --> User : Email vérifié → redirection login

== Connexion ==

User -> Browser : Formulaire de connexion
Browser -> GW : POST /api/auth/login\n{ email, password, remember_me }
GW -> AUTH : Login(email, password, remember_me)
AUTH -> DBA : SELECT FROM auth WHERE email
AUTH -> AUTH : Vérification bcrypt(password, hash)
AUTH -> AUTH : Génération access_token (JWT, ~2 min)\n+ refresh_token (7j / 60j si remember_me)
AUTH -> DBA : INSERT INTO refresh_tokens\n(user_id, token_hash, expires_at, remember_me)
AUTH -> USERS : TouchUserLastLogin(user_id)
AUTH --> GW : LoginResponse\n(access_token, refresh_token)
GW --> Browser : 200 + Set-Cookie (refresh_token httpOnly)
Browser --> User : Connecté → Dashboard

== Appel API protégé ==

Browser -> GW : GET /api/quotes\n(Authorization: Bearer access_token)
GW -> AUTH : IntrospectToken(access_token)
AUTH -> AUTH : Vérification JWT (signature + expiry)\n+ vérifie session_version
AUTH --> GW : AccessContext\n{ user_id, email, role, account_status,\n  subscription_tier, session_version,\n  email_verified }
GW -> GW : Contrôle d'autorisation (authz)
note right of GW : Autorisé → proxy vers Quote svc

== Refresh automatique (401) ==

Browser -> GW : GET /api/quotes (access_token expiré)
GW -> AUTH : IntrospectToken(access_token)
AUTH --> GW : Erreur 1004 (token invalide)
GW --> Browser : 401

note over Browser
  apiFetch() dans front/lib/api.ts
  intercepte le 401 et déclenche
  automatiquement le refresh
end note

Browser -> GW : POST /api/auth/refresh\n(refresh_token depuis cookie)
GW -> AUTH : RefreshToken(refresh_token)
AUTH -> DBA : SELECT FROM refresh_tokens\n  WHERE token_hash AND expires_at > NOW()
AUTH -> AUTH : Génération nouveau access_token\n(+ rotation refresh_token)
AUTH -> DBA : DELETE ancien refresh_token\nINSERT nouveau refresh_token
AUTH --> GW : LoginResponse (nouveaux tokens)
GW --> Browser : 200 + Set-Cookie (nouveau refresh_token)

Browser -> GW : Rejoue GET /api/quotes\n(nouveau access_token)
GW --> Browser : 200

== Déconnexion ==

User -> Browser : "Se déconnecter"
Browser -> GW : POST /api/auth/logout
GW -> AUTH : Logout(refresh_token)
AUTH -> DBA : DELETE FROM refresh_tokens WHERE token_hash
AUTH --> GW : OK
GW --> Browser : 200 + Clear-Cookie
Browser --> User : Redirigé vers /login

== Invalidation de session (changement de rôle/tier) ==

note over AUTH, DBA
  Lors d'un UpdateSubscriptionTier ou UpdateRole :
  ALTER TABLE auth SET session_version = session_version + 1
  → tous les refresh_tokens existants sont invalidés
  → IntrospectToken échoue avec code 1008 (SESSION_INVALIDATED)
  → front redirige vers /login
end note

@enduml
